Conflicts between the devtoolverse and other packages

Source: R/verse.R
devtoolverse_conflicts.Rd

This function lists all the conflicts between packages in the devtoolverse and other packages that you have loaded.

devtoolverse_conflicts()

Details

If dplyr is one of the select packages, then the following four conflicts are deliberately ignored: intersect, union, setequal, and setdiff from dplyr. These functions make the base equivalents generic, so shouldn't negatively affect any existing code.

Examples
